radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bilateral lower lobe atelectasis. A 0.4 cm nodule in the left lower lobe. Fluid-filled and dilated appendix measuring up to 10 mm with subtle fat stranding, thickening of lateral conal fascia, a 0.5 cm appendicolith, and mucosal hyperemia, consistent with early appendicitis. No evidence of focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, or kidneys. Small amount of free fluid in the pelvis.
